    "name": "M-Walk",
    "description": "M-Walk is a graph-walking agent designed for applications like Knowledge Base Completion (KBC) that addresses the problem of sparse rewards. Architecturally, it consists of a deep recurrent neural network (RNN) and Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS). The RNN processes the state (history of the walked path) and outputs both a policy and Q-values. To train effectively from sparse rewards, M-Walk combines MCTS with the neural policy to generate trajectories that yield more positive rewards. It is trained by improving the network in an off-policy manner using Q-learning, modifying the RNN policy through parameter sharing; this process is iteratively applied for model learning. At test time, MCTS and the neural policy are combined to predict the target node. Experimental results show that M-Walk achieves better policies than other RL-based methods, particularly those based on policy gradients, and outperforms traditional KBC baselines.",
    "keywords": [
        "graph-walking agent",
        "knowledge base completion (KBC)",
        "reinforcement learning (RL)",
        "M-Walk",
